<info>
Olmecs were first major mesoamerican civilization dating between 1600 and 400 BC.
They are known the most of building huge head sculptures and spreading their ritual ball game in the region.
Little is known about them, their writing system has not been deciphered and there is no source describing their beliefs
and religion.

Olmec trait is Religious, to represent their art and ritual traditions which have later spread and influenced other mesoamerican
civilzations.

Olmec leaders are their gods - no list of Olmec leaders has been found.
Olmec color is grey - the color of stone, which they have made their giant heads of.
</info>
